My Lord gives me selfless love in my youth;
Leads me to wisdom, eternal truth.
Our hearts weave the friendships of logosians;
Be grateful, the joyful ones.
We tread the Road of Truth for Honesty, Kindness, Beauty all our lives.
Open our windows wide for the world outside;
Innovations fill our curious minds.
We pledge to serve teh world whole-heartedly,
Shining like the Pilar Beams.
Embrace life challenges; pursue our dreams;
Lead the world; beam love across the land.
Lead our lives for the glory of the Lord.

Led by God's graciousness, we march;
Prove our school motto worthy of charge;
Just as Christ for us sinners lay down His life,
We, as salt, as light, witness His love,
Be respectful to teachers and friends;
Pray together:"O Lord, take our hands;
Open our eyes to knowledge and gifts assigned,
Build our lives to serve the kingdom of Thine."

records.中文校歌歌詞:
有膝都當跪下,崇拜耶穌名;
有舌都當承認,祂是榮耀君。
祂是太初真道,祂是真光明;
我們稱祂基督,乃父所歡欣。
歡然舉祂名字,建校蔡功譜;
教育我眾孩童,傳揚主真道
秉承忠誠仁愛,立我懿行高;
服膺我主引導,唯主名是從。

records.英文校歌歌詞:
1. All through our College a voice is resounding; promptly respond to your duty’s clean call;
harken you all for the trumpet is sounding;
your Mater’s proclaiming her watchword to all.
2. "Labour and VIrtue" your motto still bearing;
forward with courage in ways that are just;
true to your standard be doing and daring, as faithful Josephians in Heaven you trust.
3. Onward and upward in life's earnest battle, joyously bearing the brunt of the fight;
nobly forgiving for aught that may pain you, and bravely defending the course of the right.
4. Lift up your hearts for a Kingdom awaits you, honour and virtue with courage defend;
serve Him in life who in death can reward you, and vow to be faithful and true to the end.
(Repeat)
Forward, no flinch nor fear, ever with hearts sincere, render with joy to your mater her due; all that is vile reject; heaven will e’er protect, sons of st. Joseph’s valiant and true.

1. Once to every man and nation, Comes the moment to decide,
In the strife of truth with falsehood, For the good or evil side;
Some great cause, some new decision, Offering each the bloom or blight,
And the choice goes by forever. Twixt that darkness and that light.
2. Then to side with truth is noble, When we share her wretched crust, Ere her cause bring fame and profit, And 'tis prosperous to be just;
Then it is the brave man chooses. While the coward stands aside,
Till the multitude make virtue Of the faith they had denied.
3. Though the cause of evil prosper, Yet 'tis truth alone is strong;
Though her portion be the scaffold. And upon the throng be wrong;
Yet that scaffold sways the future, And behind the dim unknown,
Stand-eth God within the shadow Keeping watch above His own.

Bless this house. O Lord we pray, Make it safe by night end day;
Bless there walls, so firm and stout, Keeping want and trouble out;
Bless the roof and chimneys tall. Let Thy peace lie over all;
Bless this door, that it may prove Ever open to joy and love;
Bless these windows shining bright. Let-ting in God's heav'nly light;
Bless the hearth a-blazing there, With smoke ascending like a prayer;
Bless the people here within, Keep them pure and free from sin;
Bless us all that we may be Fit, O Lord, to dwell with Thee,
Bless us all that we one day May dwell. O Lord, with Thee.
